{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-awesome-all-timeline-js","path":"/2022/07/21/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"Track Awesome List"}},"allAwesomeItem":{"nodes":[{"awesomeListRepo":"avelino/awesome-go","categoryHTML":"<h2>Authentication and OAuth</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/ory/keto\">keto</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/ory/keto\" style=\"text-decoration:none;top: -2px;position: relative;margin-left:4px;margin-right:4px;font-weight:400;\"><span style=\"color: #fff;font-size: 11px;font-family: Verdana, Geneva, DejaVu Sans,sans-serif;\"><span style=\"padding:4px 4px 4px 6px;background: #555;border-top-left-radius: 4px;border-bottom-left-radius: 4px;\">stars</span><span style=\"padding: 4px 6px 4px 4px;background: #007ec6;border-top-right-radius: 4px;border-bottom-right-radius: 4px;\">3.6k</span></span></a><!--TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_START____{\"type\":\"repo\",\"stargazerCount\":3624,\"repo\":\"ory/keto\"}____TRACK_AWESOME_REPO_ITEM_END--> - Open Source (Go) implementation of \"Zanzibar: Google's Consistent, Global Authorization System\". Ships gRPC, REST APIs, newSQL, and an easy and granular permission language. Supports ACL, RBAC, and other access models.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-21T17:05:49.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=cYP8TcokSFI\">Streaming three ways with Blazor: REST, gRPC, and SignalR</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-45%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> April 29, 2022 - Streaming three ways with Blazor: REST, gRPC, and SignalR, by Carl Franklin at the NDC Porto 2022. Learn how to stream data from server to client to improve perceived performance and increase scalability. Carl shows how streaming works in general, and then how to implement using each of these three transports.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-21T11:43:15.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=L9p-9dGp-98\">State management in Blazor</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-63%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> April 29, 2022 - State management in Blazor, at the NDC Porto 2022. When developing a Single Page Application, a very important aspect is state management. Since Blazer is a component-based UI framework, how do we manage to update the UI when the state of the application changes.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-21T11:40:21.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=RevmsFXVJ5Q\">Making Blazor work with everything, plus WebAssembly on the server</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-60%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> May 13, 2022 - Talk by Steve Sanderson at the NDC London 2022. Real-world software projects often involve combining many technologies. So, is modern Blazor powerful and flexible enough for your team's needs? In this demo-heavy talk, Steve will show how Blazor WebAssembly/Server can seamlessly embed libraries and logic written in other languages such as Rust or C/C++, how Blazor WebAssembly/Server components can be used inside other SPA frameworks such as React or Angular (or vice-versa) and how Blazor components can be used not only for web projects, but also shared with native apps for macOS, iOS, Android, and Windows (including WPF and WinForms) These capabilities should equip your team to take on the most ambitious projects with confidence. We'll then look further into the future and consider how WebAssembly is moving beyond the browser and is pitched to become a foundational element of cloud-native server apps. You'll be among the first to see an experimental new approach to compiling .NET applications into WASI-compliant universal binaries that can run on any OS or processor, robustly sandboxed and with great performance.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-21T11:36:24.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Videos</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3fLoxkuzzqo\">Building apps for Teams in .NET &#x26; Blazor</a> - <img src=\"https://img.shields.io/badge/Duration:%20-17%20min-%230094FF?style=flat-square&#x26;cacheSeconds=maxAge&#x26;logo=youtube\" alt=\"duration\"> May 11, 2022 - John Miller joins James on this week's On .NET to chat about how .NET developers can build Microsoft Teams apps and bots completely with C#, .NET, and Blazor! John walks us through everything we need to know to get started and how to even publish apps for Teams.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-21T11:36:24.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://engstromjimmy.com/post/2022-07-21-ShareBlazorComponentsUsingDi\">Share Blazor components using dependency injection</a> - July 19, 2022 - Share Blazor components using dependency injection.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-21T10:02:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"AdrienTorris/awesome-blazor","categoryHTML":"<h2>Articles</h2>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://www.meziantou.net/using-iasyncenumerable-in-a-razor-component.htm\">Using IAsyncEnumerable in a Razor component</a> - July 18, 2022 - Using IAsyncEnumerable in a Razor component.</li>","updatedAt":"2022-07-21T10:02:16.000Z"},{"awesomeListRepo":"vuejs/awesome-vue","categoryHTML":"<h2>Components &#x26; Libraries</h2><h4>Responsive</h4>","itemHTML":"<li><a href=\"https://github.com/vueComponent/ant-design-vue\">ant-design-vue</a><a data-role=\"trackawesomelist-badge\" href=\"https://github.com/vueComponent/ant-design-vue\" style=\"text-decora